where West and the others are...

232
00:18:06,718 --> 00:18:09,152
...and can they be found?

233
00:18:10,289 --> 00:18:12,519
There's no need.

234
00:18:13,525 --> 00:18:15,186
They're dead, aren't they?

235
00:18:18,163 --> 00:18:19,425
Yes, sir.

236
00:18:20,132 --> 00:18:21,531
You kill them?

237
00:18:32,377 --> 00:18:35,938
Look, we got enough on you
to deep-fry your ass!

238
00:18:36,115 --> 00:18:37,980
Back to silent treatment, fine by me.

239
00:18:38,150 --> 00:18:41,051
-l'm just gonna have to haul your ass--
-Okay, whoa. Time-out.

240
00:18:41,220 --> 00:18:45,020
Look, Ray, this is what you call
''good cop-bad cop.''

241
00:18:45,190 --> 00:18:48,751
She shouts. l stand up for you.
You're grateful.

242
00:18:48,927 --> 00:18:51,794
This establishes
some sort of bond of trust.

243
00:18:51,964 --> 00:18:53,864
l don't wanna play games with you...

244
00:18:54,032 --> 00:18:58,628
...so l say we take a break. Okay?
And get you another donut.

245
00:18:58,804 --> 00:19:00,931
You see if you wanna talk anymore.

246
00:19:04,209 --> 00:19:06,769
-''Deep-fry your ass''?
-You set me up.

247
00:19:06,945 --> 00:19:08,913
l believe somebody owes me 10 bucks.

248
00:19:09,081 --> 00:19:11,606
You could have told me
what you were planning.

249
00:19:11,783 --> 00:19:13,614
Everybody knows good cop-bad cop.

250
00:19:13,785 --> 00:19:15,582
By admitting it,
l could gain his trust.

251
00:19:18,290 --> 00:19:21,726
-You think he did it?
-No, sir.

252
00:19:22,694 --> 00:19:24,161
Yes.

253
00:19:25,130 --> 00:19:27,758
What about the rest of my people?

254
00:19:31,036 --> 00:19:35,598
ln 5 1/2 hours, it'll be out of our hands.
l'm gonna have a lot to answer for.

255
00:19:35,774 --> 00:19:38,743
l'd appreciate it if you could get me
some of those answers.

256
00:19:41,046 --> 00:19:45,039
-Why did you ask for a Ranger?
-l'm not telling you what happened.

257
00:19:45,217 --> 00:19:47,208
Why don't you tell us about the others?

258
00:19:47,386 --> 00:19:50,116
Tell us about the course.
Tell us about Sergeant West.

259
00:19:50,289 --> 00:19:52,120
ls he still the same prick?

260
00:19:52,291 --> 00:19:55,852
l do not care
that you are triple volunteers.

261
00:19:56,028 --> 00:19:59,520
l do not care
that you think you are hard.

262
00:19:59,698 --> 00:20:04,067
And l especially don't give a rat's fuck
what four-star general's dick...

263
00:20:04,236 --> 00:20:08,297
...you sucked to get the privilege
of being able stand before me today.

264
00:20:09,274 --> 00:20:14,712
Those of you l deem unworthy
will not remain.

265
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:17,747
ls that understood?
Can l get a ''Hoo-ha, sergeant''?

266
00:20:17,916 --> 00:20:19,178
Hoo-ha, sergeant!

267
00:20:19,351 --> 00:20:22,650
Those of you l find lacking will quit.

268
00:20:22,821 --> 00:20:27,781
And those of you who refuse to quit
will have a training accident.

269
00:20:27,960 --> 00:20:31,157
This base suffers
three training accidents a year.

270
00:20:31,330 --> 00:20:35,164
Unfortunate accidents that l will not
hesitate to repeat...

271
00:20:35,634 --> 00:20:39,263
...if you cross me. ls that understood?

272
00:20:39,438 --> 00:20:42,896
-Give me a ''Hoo-ha, sergeant.''
-Hoo-ha, sergeant!

273
00:20:43,075 --> 00:20:46,135
-And what's your name?
-Sergeant, my name is Pike, sergeant.

274
00:20:46,311 --> 00:20:50,179
Pike, surrender your sidearm
for inspection.

275
00:20:50,349 --> 00:20:53,750
What the fuck are you doing?
Have you lost your fucking mind?

276
00:20:53,919 --> 00:20:57,320
-You told me to relinquish--
-Are you talking? Did you speak to me?

277
00:20:57,689 --> 00:20:59,714
Who the fuck told you to speak?!

278
00:20:59,891 --> 00:21:02,826
A Ranger never relinquishes
his weapon!

279
00:21:02,995 --> 00:21:06,021
lf George S. Motherfucking Patton
rises from his holy grave...

280
00:21:06,198 --> 00:21:09,998
...and asks you for your weapon,
you will not surrender your weapon.

281
00:21:10,168 --> 00:21:12,329
Everybody better give me
a ''Hoo-ha, sergeant.''

282
00:21:12,504 --> 00:21:14,768
-Hoo-ha, sergeant!
-Now, son...

283
00:21:14,940 --> 00:21:18,501
...there are people in this world
that will kill you for no damn reason...

284
00:21:18,677 --> 00:21:21,271
...other than something
passing through their mind!

285
00:21:21,446 --> 00:21:25,439
l hail from Biloxi, Mississippi,
where vanilla motherfuckers like that...

286
00:21:25,617 --> 00:21:28,950
...used to hang us from trees
by our necks on a whim!

287
00:21:29,354 --> 00:21:32,721
Does that sound like the kind
of fucking place you want to grow up?

288
00:21:32,891 --> 00:21:34,153
Sergeant, no, sergeant!

289
00:21:34,326 --> 00:21:38,160
Are you implying something negative
about the great state of Mississippi?

290
00:21:38,330 --> 00:21:42,198
From the beginning, West had a chip
on his shoulder for this guy named Pike.

291
00:21:44,036 --> 00:21:48,029
By the time we did Green Hell,
it was getting nuts.

292
00:21:48,473 --> 00:21:51,465
Green Hell was 20 days
in the Darien at 40 clicks a day...

293
00:21:51,643 --> 00:21:53,543
...with an 80-pound pack on your back.

294
00:21:53,712 --> 00:21:56,010
We got real used
to number oddities like that.

295
00:21:56,748 --> 00:21:59,182
The course was called Jungle Leader
and the idea...

296
00:21:59,351 --> 00:22:02,411
...was to teach you how to think
when you were exhausted.

297
00:22:02,721 --> 00:22:05,246
And West really knew
how to get you exhausted.

298
00:22:08,160 --> 00:22:10,424
We spent our nights
doing escape and evasions...

299
00:22:10,595 --> 00:22:12,529
...with live fire snapping by our heads...

300
00:22:12,698 --> 00:22:14,859
...or else up to our noses in
some damn swamp...

301
00:22:15,033 --> 00:22:17,001
...slapping bugs and dodging snakes.

302
00:22:17,669 --> 00:22:22,163
The nights we did mock POW stuff,
they wouldn't let us sleep at all.

303
00:22:26,778 --> 00:22:29,440
We humped over the Cordillera
three times...

304
00:22:29,614 --> 00:22:32,242
...all the way to the Colombian border
and back.

305
00:22:32,417 --> 00:22:37,286
Some of that stuff is steep as hell
and the rain never let up for days.

306
00:22:38,056 --> 00:22:39,717
Those packs got heavy in the rain...

307
00:22:39,891 --> 00:22:44,260
...and nobody ever hated anything
like we hated those damn packs.

308
00:22:45,263 --> 00:22:48,255
There was this one escarpment,
it wasn't more than 500 feet...

309
00:22:48,433 --> 00:22:50,230
...but, Jesus, it was slippery.

310
00:22:50,402 --> 00:22:50,535
Mr. Pike...

311
00:22:50,535 --> 00:22:52,264
Mr. Pike...

312
00:22:52,437 --> 00:22:55,270
...can you tell me the muzzle velocity
of an M-16?

313
00:22:56,875 --> 00:22:58,433
Yeah.

314
00:23:01,680 --> 00:23:04,808
-Eleven hundred, sergeant.
-Eleven hundred what?

315
00:23:06,284 --> 00:23:08,479
Meters per second, sergeant.

316
00:23:08,653 --> 00:23:11,383
Take 40% of that
and multiply it by the exact number...

317
00:23:11,556 --> 00:23:13,888
...of each animal Moses
took with him on the Ark.

318
00:23:17,996 --> 00:23:20,726
-Come on.
-Twenty....

319
00:23:21,600 --> 00:23:24,694
Come on. You tired, Mr. Pike?
Too tired to think?

320
00:23:24,870 --> 00:23:28,328
Zero, schmuck.
Moses wasn't on the Ark.

321
00:23:28,673 --> 00:23:30,903
Have you lost it?

322
00:23:31,076 --> 00:23:33,067
Well, tell me this.

323
00:23:33,512 --> 00:23:35,446
What is your weapon?

324
00:23:36,982 --> 00:23:39,280
Your weapon, man. Your weapon.

325
00:23:39,651 --> 00:23:43,018
What keeps you alive
and makes the other guy die?

326
00:23:43,188 --> 00:23:46,624
What is your weapon?

327
00:23:47,626 --> 00:23:49,594
lt's your brain, Mr. Pike.

328
00:23:49,761 --> 00:23:52,559
Your noggin. Your noodle.
Your smarts. Your gray matter.

329
00:23:52,731 --> 00:23:54,858
Your poise under fire.

330
00:23:55,033 --> 00:23:59,697
Your wits, when all about you
are losing theirs.

331
00:23:59,871 --> 00:24:03,602
l think you came to this party
unarmed, Mr. Pike.

332
00:24:04,109 --> 00:24:06,202
Take off your pack.

333
00:24:07,412 --> 00:24:08,936
Take it off.

334
00:24:14,953 --> 00:24:17,649
Here, l'll help you. Come on.

335
00:24:33,738 --> 00:24:38,004
You can't complete this march
without a pack, Mr. Pike.

336
00:24:38,176 --> 00:24:44,445
l suggest you go back and get it,
even if it takes 40 days and 40 nights.

337
00:24:46,485 --> 00:24:48,715
That business bothered
a lot of the guys...

338
00:24:49,221 --> 00:24:52,918
...even Mueller, who was a redneck
you felt uncomfortable sleeping around.

339
00:24:53,091 --> 00:24:54,319
Dumb shit.

340
00:25:02,934 --> 00:25:06,734
So that's what we were coming back
from yesterday afternoon.

341
00:25:07,572 --> 00:25:11,099
We figured we'd finally get
a shower and a hot meal.

342
00:25:11,476 --> 00:25:14,070
l mean, we were the walking dead.

343
00:25:14,246 --> 00:25:17,738
We were about as ragged-out
as a man could ever get.

344
00:25:24,589 --> 00:25:26,614
Here comes Master West himself.

345
00:25:30,929 --> 00:25:34,592
What we have here is an opportunity.

346
00:25:34,766 --> 00:25:38,497
A unique opportunity
for a spectacular training event.

347
00:25:38,670 --> 00:25:42,538
Dunbar. Kendall.
Mueller. Nunez. Castro.

348
00:25:42,707 --> 00:25:47,906
Drop your packs. Weapons only.
Muster at the east LZ in two minutes.

349
00:25:48,079 --> 00:25:50,707
-Jesus Christ.
-What was that, Mr. Pike?

350
00:25:52,717 --> 00:25:55,277
You think a little rain
is inappropriate for combat?

351
00:25:55,453 --> 00:25:57,853
That the game should be called
on account of weather?

352
00:25:58,023 --> 00:25:59,923
Are you concerned for their safety?

353
00:26:00,225 --> 00:26:01,590
Sergeant....

354
00:26:03,161 --> 00:26:04,651
What?

355
00:26:06,298 --> 00:26:11,292
-No, sergeant.
-Good, then you can join them.

356
00:26:13,538 --> 00:26:16,098
Those are the guys that went
on the exercise with you?

357
00:26:17,375 --> 00:26:20,503
Yeah, and that is all l'm saying.

358
00:26:23,848 --> 00:26:25,110
Ray?

359
00:26:29,254 --> 00:26:30,778
You smoke?

360
00:26:30,956 --> 00:26:34,619
ls this a trick where you won't
give me a cigarette till l tell you more?

361
00:26:34,793 --> 00:26:38,160
No, l just forgot mine in the car,
and l was hoping that you had some.

362
00:26:43,268 --> 00:26:45,634
My brand. My lucky day.

363
00:26:52,377 --> 00:26:54,208
You seem like a good guy, Ray.

364
00:26:54,379 --> 00:26:57,507
You carried Kendall
wounded to the pickup...

365
00:26:57,682 --> 00:26:59,377
...but l just don't understand.

366
00:26:59,551 --> 00:27:03,043
What did you do to make
Mueller want to kill you?

367
00:27:05,590 --> 00:27:07,524
l'm not saying anything else.

368
00:27:12,497 --> 00:27:16,058
l just don't understand
why he asked for a Ranger.

369
00:27:16,234 --> 00:27:19,965
The man's in trouble.
Never leave a man behind.

370
00:27:20,138 --> 00:27:23,574
-So?
-Ranger code.

371
00:27:24,009 --> 00:27:26,773
Never leave a man behind.

372
00:27:27,612 --> 00:27:29,546
What's the matter?

373
00:27:31,983 --> 00:27:34,645
This place gives me the willies.

374
00:27:34,819 --> 00:27:38,084
-Not the happiest of memories, huh?
-No.

375
00:27:40,725 --> 00:27:43,694
He's the son of a general,
so go easy on him. Kid gloves.

376
00:27:43,862 --> 00:27:45,989
-All right.
-l mean it. Kid gloves.

377
00:27:46,164 --> 00:27:47,995
l got it.

378
00:27:48,767 --> 00:27:51,497
Yeah. Thanks.

379
00:27:51,970 --> 00:27:53,767
Tommy, that you?

380
00:27:53,938 --> 00:27:56,498
Pete Vilmer, as l live and breathe.
How are you?

381
00:27:56,675 --> 00:27:59,337
-How are you? l'm good.
-Osborne, Pete Vilmer.

382
00:27:59,511 --> 00:28:02,344
l know. Let me guess,
you two trained together?

383
00:28:02,514 --> 00:28:04,914
Guilty as charged, Julie-bird.
What are you doing here?

384
00:28:05,083 --> 00:28:08,052
-You're not getting all nostalgic on me?
-No, l can't tell you--

385
00:28:08,219 --> 00:28:09,709
-l'm running this joint.
-No.

386
00:28:09,888 --> 00:28:12,686
Yeah. We're busy as hell too.
Packing up supplies...

387
00:28:12,857 --> 00:28:14,688
...getting ready for the move stateside.

388
00:28:14,859 --> 00:28:17,123
Who'd have thunk it?
Pete Vilmer, bettering society.

389
00:28:17,295 --> 00:28:19,695
Shall we see Kendall
or would you like to continue...

390
00:28:19,864 --> 00:28:21,923
...the backslapping
for a couple of minutes?

391
00:28:22,100 --> 00:28:24,091
''Julie-bird.''

392
00:28:24,269 --> 00:28:27,602
Now if l were a smart man,
and l am not...

393
00:28:27,772 --> 00:28:33,608
...l could come to the conclusion
that you two saw each other socially.

394
00:28:34,479 --> 00:28:38,575
Oh, l've seen you around
the base before, but...

395
00:28:38,917 --> 00:28:43,320
...well, are you in the Army or...?

396
00:28:43,488 --> 00:28:46,218
Coast Guard.
We're worried about Florida beaches.

397
00:28:46,391 --> 00:28:50,623
Oh, l've seen you before.
You were in the newspaper.

398
00:28:50,795 --> 00:28:54,424
You're that DEA agent
with friends in low places.

399
00:28:54,599 --> 00:28:56,897
Oh, the price of fame.

400
00:28:57,068 --> 00:28:59,901
We were wondering if you'd
answer a few questions for us?

401
00:29:01,339 --> 00:29:06,470
Oh, no. l'm really fatigued.
l feel all drugged-up.

402
00:29:06,644 --> 00:29:09,545
Our collective hearts weep.

403
00:29:09,714 --> 00:29:12,342
Well, we just wanna know
what happened out there.

404
00:29:12,517 --> 00:29:15,680
Oh, you wanna know what happened?

405
00:29:16,221 --> 00:29:18,655
Well, there are degrees of truth, captain.

406
00:29:18,823 --> 00:29:23,317
You know, there are always degrees
and things are not what they seem.

407
00:29:23,495 --> 00:29:25,087
You know, this is--

408
00:29:25,263 --> 00:29:27,663
lt is too late and l am too tired
to give a shit...

409
00:29:27,832 --> 00:29:31,393
...about some pissant lieutenant's
bad version of intrigue.

410
00:29:31,569 --> 00:29:35,198
You're trying too hard, Levi.
You know how l can tell?

411
00:29:35,373 --> 00:29:37,773
Because you're sweating,
and you're sweating...

412
00:29:37,942 --> 00:29:41,605
...because you don't know
how much Dunbar told us already.

413
00:29:43,548 --> 00:29:45,038
Excuse me.

414
00:29:49,621 --> 00:29:53,182
-Those were kid gloves?
-l thought l did pretty well up till the end.

415
00:29:53,358 --> 00:29:55,724
You mean when you yelled
at him and walked out?

416
00:29:55,894 --> 00:30:00,228
Well, that would be the end, yeah.
We'll play it differently when we go back.

417
00:30:00,398 --> 00:30:02,889
Go back? We just blew it.

418
00:30:04,235 --> 00:30:07,432
-l thought you didn't have any cigarettes.
-l lied.

419
00:30:07,605 --> 00:30:10,904
-Will you just wait? Just wait.
-For what?

420
00:30:12,243 --> 00:30:16,009
Excuse me. A patient is asking for you.

421
00:30:16,447 --> 00:30:18,381
Shall we?

422
00:30:20,285 --> 00:30:23,118
My father is what you would call
a very powerful man.

423
00:30:23,288 --> 00:30:28,385
-So we've heard.
-Oh, come on, you know...

424
00:30:28,560 --> 00:30:30,585
...you don't know the half of it.
l mean....

425
00:30:30,762 --> 00:30:36,928
You know, all my life he's made me
feel weak and insignificant.

426
00:30:38,603 --> 00:30:43,404
Yeah, l think that is reason why l joined
the military in the first place.

427
00:30:43,575 --> 00:30:45,702
And how is that going for you?

428
00:30:45,877 --> 00:30:49,335
Oh, it's horrible.
l fucking hate the military.

429
00:30:50,014 --> 00:30:52,574
You're terrified of him, aren't you?

430
00:30:54,285 --> 00:30:56,753
No, no, we just hate each other.

431
00:30:58,923 --> 00:31:05,158
You know, and normally he wouldn't
lift a finger to do anything for me...

432
00:31:07,899 --> 00:31:11,062
...but the one thing he cannot
stand is a scandal...

433
00:31:11,236 --> 00:31:15,138
...and you know, a joint chief...

434
00:31:15,306 --> 00:31:20,107
...with a homosexual son in the military
definitely qualifies as scandal.

435
00:31:20,278 --> 00:31:23,076
Well, that blows ''Don't ask,
don't tell'' out of the water.

436
00:31:23,281 --> 00:31:26,876
So is this family history lesson
coming to a point?

437
00:31:27,552 --> 00:31:33,752
About four months ago,
l began a relationship with a local...

438
00:31:34,359 --> 00:31:40,264
...and my father decided to
intercede. And Colonel Styles...

439
00:31:40,431 --> 00:31:45,198
...made the incident quiet.
But according to my father...

440
00:31:45,370 --> 00:31:48,237
...transferred me into
West's training course.

441
00:31:48,406 --> 00:31:51,273
And, you know, West just hated that.

442
00:31:51,442 --> 00:31:54,172
He made sure everyone
knew where l was and all that.

443
00:31:54,345 --> 00:31:57,439
Couldn't kick you out so he
wanted you to quit on your own.

444
00:31:58,316 --> 00:32:00,682
Well, he wanted more than that.

445
00:32:00,852 --> 00:32:03,650
More intrigue, Levi?

446
00:32:04,689 --> 00:32:06,088
Yes.

447
00:32:07,759 --> 00:32:14,164
l swear to God, you will swim the
canal! The teams are as follows...

448
00:32:14,666 --> 00:32:17,430
Dunbar and...

449
00:32:18,469 --> 00:32:20,937
...Mueller.

450
00:32:21,339 --> 00:32:24,775
Pike and Nunez.

451
00:32:26,010 --> 00:32:28,205
Kendall and...

452
00:32:28,379 --> 00:32:29,903
...Castro.

453
00:32:30,081 --> 00:32:35,417
You have one minute to touch down.
Get your shit together!

454
00:32:36,321 --> 00:32:38,482
That's when he did it.

455
00:32:44,362 --> 00:32:47,354
He was threatening my life.
lt was clear as day.

456
00:32:48,766 --> 00:32:51,394
Did anyone else see
or hear this?

457
00:32:51,569 --> 00:32:54,800
No, of course not. There
was a helicopter, you know?

458
00:32:54,973 --> 00:32:58,238
-Nobody could hear anything.
-l don't know how familiar you are...

459
00:32:58,409 --> 00:33:01,537
...with investigative work,
but there's this thing called motive.

460
00:33:02,313 --> 00:33:04,213
And you just gave yourself one.

461
00:33:04,382 --> 00:33:07,818
Well, you wanted to know
what happened...

462
00:33:07,986 --> 00:33:11,888
-...and l'm telling you the truth.
-What happened to degrees?

463
00:33:14,459 --> 00:33:16,324
l didn't kill him.

464
00:33:18,363 --> 00:33:20,024
Then who did?

465
00:33:23,401 --> 00:33:25,426
Thirty seconds to LZ.

466
00:33:25,603 --> 00:33:29,369
Click in! On the skids!
Lose the communicators!

