01:08:31,140 --> 01:08:33,904
You're relieved of your duties
until further notice.

931
01:08:34,143 --> 01:08:36,668
-Yes, sir.
-You'll be lucky if l don't put you in...

932
01:08:36,846 --> 01:08:38,404
...for a court-martial.

933
01:08:39,949 --> 01:08:42,975
-He was dirty, Bill.
-He's dead, Tom!

934
01:08:43,152 --> 01:08:45,450
And don't think you're not
on my shit-list too.

935
01:08:46,288 --> 01:08:50,190
We found the bunker. lt was
demolished, like they said. No bodies.

936
01:08:50,860 --> 01:08:54,261
Come on, a hurricane like that could've
blown them three counties away.

937
01:08:54,430 --> 01:08:56,022
What happens to Dunbar now?

938
01:08:56,765 --> 01:09:00,257
ln 10 minutes he gets on a plane,
which means you're done.

939
01:09:00,436 --> 01:09:03,371
You'll understand
if l don't walk you out.

940
01:09:07,176 --> 01:09:10,009
-Strange kid.
-What?

941
01:09:10,179 --> 01:09:12,113
Kendall.

942
01:09:12,281 --> 01:09:16,012
Even while he was dying
he was making jokes about infinity.

943
01:09:25,661 --> 01:09:26,923
What?

944
01:09:33,502 --> 01:09:35,265
What?

945
01:09:37,039 --> 01:09:40,236
Dunbar wrote this when
he asked for a Ranger.

946
01:09:40,409 --> 01:09:42,001
There's an 8 on it.

947
01:09:51,654 --> 01:09:53,053
l don't know.

948
01:09:53,822 --> 01:09:55,551
Okay.

949
01:09:56,292 --> 01:09:58,487
l'll find out by myself.

950
01:09:58,661 --> 01:10:00,492
Stop.

951
01:10:04,166 --> 01:10:05,997
Okay.

952
01:10:11,740 --> 01:10:11,840
Any spooks involved here?
ClA? FBl?

953
01:10:11,840 --> 01:10:15,139
Any spooks involved here?
ClA? FBl?

954
01:10:15,711 --> 01:10:17,144
Not exactly.

955
01:10:17,546 --> 01:10:21,539
-What's that mean?
-There was a group of guys down here....

956
01:10:23,619 --> 01:10:27,214
There was a group of guys down here
who were way out on the hairy edge.

957
01:10:27,389 --> 01:10:29,949
They did covert stuff and they--

958
01:10:30,626 --> 01:10:33,459
They what?

959
01:10:33,629 --> 01:10:36,723
They went rogue. They went renegade.

960
01:10:36,899 --> 01:10:39,959
Dropped off the face of the earth,
disappeared into drug land...

961
01:10:40,135 --> 01:10:44,936
...and with their special skills cut one hell
of a swath through the competition.

962
01:10:45,107 --> 01:10:48,270
West trained some of these guys.

963
01:10:48,444 --> 01:10:51,277
And he hated them for what they did,
and they hated him.

964
01:10:51,847 --> 01:10:54,941
-That could be what this is about.
-Who knows about this?

965
01:10:55,117 --> 01:10:57,779
How do l know?
They're ghosts, right? They're dead.

966
01:10:57,953 --> 01:11:01,286
This could all be a story.
None of this could be true.

967
01:11:01,857 --> 01:11:06,191
But the note that that kid wrote...

968
01:11:06,362 --> 01:11:08,125
...had an 8 on it.

969
01:11:09,198 --> 01:11:11,666
And that's what this outfit
called themselves.

970
01:11:12,868 --> 01:11:14,836
Section 8.

971
01:11:15,037 --> 01:11:18,973
Section 8?
You mean, like, they're crazy?

972
01:11:22,478 --> 01:11:26,812
-How could you keep that from me?
-Classified.

973
01:11:30,419 --> 01:11:35,618
You son of a bitch!
Mister, l've had it with you!

974
01:11:39,094 --> 01:11:41,324
Okay, so are you happy?

975
01:11:55,144 --> 01:11:56,805
ls that a no?

976
01:12:04,086 --> 01:12:07,487
Ma'am. Need your signature
for this guy's transport.

977
01:12:07,656 --> 01:12:09,146
Sure thing.

978
01:12:09,391 --> 01:12:11,518
What the hell happened to you two?

979
01:12:11,727 --> 01:12:15,686
None of your business.
Kendall's dead and you're going to jail.

980
01:12:15,864 --> 01:12:17,729
ClD's here to take you to Washington.

981
01:12:17,966 --> 01:12:22,926
Guess l'm on the same transport as Pike.
Hey, Julie-bird, you bitch...

982
01:12:23,339 --> 01:12:26,433
...why don't you go on and get me
something to eat? l'm starving.

983
01:12:26,608 --> 01:12:30,009
-What did you say?
-l didn't mean to call her a bitch.

984
01:12:30,179 --> 01:12:32,579
No, no, no, before. What did you say?

985
01:12:34,049 --> 01:12:38,543
What, that me and Pike were on
a transport plane going to D.C. together?

986
01:12:39,688 --> 01:12:41,212
You mean Dunbar.

987
01:12:42,257 --> 01:12:45,556
No, Pike.

988
01:12:46,862 --> 01:12:50,525
The one that they just
hauled out of here.

989
01:12:50,699 --> 01:12:54,726
The guy that they brought in
with Kendall on the chopper.

990
01:12:54,937 --> 01:12:56,370
That was Dunbar.

991
01:12:56,905 --> 01:13:00,363
No. That's not right.

992
01:13:00,576 --> 01:13:03,067
What do you mean? Why not?

993
01:13:03,379 --> 01:13:05,176
Tom...

994
01:13:05,814 --> 01:13:08,078
...Ray Dunbar is black.

995
01:13:30,773 --> 01:13:32,832
Son of a bitch did the whole thing!

996
01:13:33,041 --> 01:13:35,202
Files don't show race.
All he had to do is switch dog tags.

997
01:13:35,377 --> 01:13:37,470
-Where's this transport going from?
-Hangar Four.

998
01:13:37,679 --> 01:13:41,171
Move it. Come on, go!
Go! Go! Go!

999
01:14:02,371 --> 01:14:04,066
-Sir!
-We got company, sir.

1000
01:14:04,239 --> 01:14:07,106
-l need to talk to your prisoner right now!
-What, captain?

1001
01:14:07,309 --> 01:14:10,710
-l need to take him back for questioning--
-We're not finished with you yet, Pike.

1002
01:14:10,879 --> 01:14:12,779
-Wanna bet?
-Let go!

1003
01:14:12,981 --> 01:14:15,541
Hey! Hardy, what the fuck
are you doing?

1004
01:14:16,385 --> 01:14:18,012
Gun!

1005
01:14:19,221 --> 01:14:23,021
-Sir! We have tried to--
-Come on down, Pike, come on down!

1006
01:14:24,159 --> 01:14:28,289
You wanna talk baseball now?
l don't think so!

1007
01:14:30,199 --> 01:14:33,498
You don't have any bodies yet!
What are you gonna do?

1008
01:14:33,669 --> 01:14:36,729
-You're not gonna shoot me!
-You see what happens when you lie?

1009
01:14:36,905 --> 01:14:39,840
What do you got?!
You got nothing on me! You got--

1010
01:14:48,684 --> 01:14:51,050
Hardy, what are you doing, man?
Stop that!

1011
01:14:51,220 --> 01:14:53,984
-Let him go!
-Stand down!

1012
01:14:54,189 --> 01:14:57,590
Tom, what the fuck are you doing?!
Stand down, goddamn it!

1013
01:15:18,113 --> 01:15:19,774
Shut up!

1014
01:15:25,687 --> 01:15:30,181
Well, well, well.
What have we got here?

1015
01:15:30,893 --> 01:15:32,986
l told you he knows.

1016
01:15:33,161 --> 01:15:35,288
Now, wait. Knows what?

1017
01:15:35,464 --> 01:15:37,091
About the other operation.

1018
01:15:38,000 --> 01:15:39,865
What other operation?

1019
01:15:40,035 --> 01:15:41,593
The coke.

1020
01:15:41,770 --> 01:15:45,638
They were sending pounds of it back
to the States, using military supply lines.

1021
01:15:46,008 --> 01:15:50,274
Vilmer would hide it in crates of files.
Hell, he'd ship it in a corpse if he had to.

1022
01:15:50,946 --> 01:15:55,406
West figured it out about a week ago.
He was gonna go to the colonel.

1023
01:15:57,085 --> 01:16:00,646
Kendall and Mueller must've decided
to take him out of the equation.

1024
01:16:00,856 --> 01:16:05,088
You have got to be the dumbest bunch
of sons of bitches on God's green earth.

1025
01:16:05,294 --> 01:16:07,785
You think you can ship that shit
right under my nose?

1026
01:16:10,432 --> 01:16:12,992
Mueller, what are you doing?!

1027
01:16:14,403 --> 01:16:15,665
Get his weapon.

1028
01:16:16,605 --> 01:16:17,629
Castro, wait!

1029
01:16:18,240 --> 01:16:19,730
Castro!

1030
01:16:21,510 --> 01:16:22,943
-Put it down.
-Fuck you, let him go!

1031
01:16:23,145 --> 01:16:25,636
This ain't some drive-by! You think
you can kill a man face to face?

1032
01:16:25,814 --> 01:16:28,248
-Put it down, Pike!
-He'll fucking shoot you!

1033
01:16:28,450 --> 01:16:32,978
l am your objective, right? You fire, l fire.
You're down to four. Well, three.

1034
01:16:33,155 --> 01:16:36,352
You can't trust him. Maybe l'll take one
or two more of you before you take me.

1035
01:16:36,525 --> 01:16:41,121
The odds are in your favor that at least
two of you walk out of here alive.

1036
01:16:41,330 --> 01:16:45,494
Conversely, there's absolutely no way l
should be able to walk out of this bunker.

1037
01:16:56,044 --> 01:16:58,842
This is bullshit! l'll do it!

1038
01:17:09,057 --> 01:17:11,252
So pretty.

1039
01:17:13,228 --> 01:17:14,661
So dead.

1040
01:17:37,085 --> 01:17:40,384
Kendall, what are you doing? Kendall!

1041
01:17:44,126 --> 01:17:46,822
What, you don't believe me?

1042
01:17:50,098 --> 01:17:56,128
Medical crate 8469846 in
Shipping D awaiting transfer.

1043
01:17:56,304 --> 01:17:58,431
See for yourself.

1044
01:18:05,047 --> 01:18:08,414
Vilmer and whoever his partner was
must have been making millions.

1045
01:18:10,519 --> 01:18:12,817
Where did the coke come from?

1046
01:18:12,988 --> 01:18:15,252
Fuck if l know.
l mean, this is Panama.

1047
01:18:15,424 --> 01:18:18,689
Throw a rock in any direction,
you'll hit three cartels.

1048
01:18:18,994 --> 01:18:22,896
About an hour later,
Kendall and l found Dunbar.

1049
01:18:42,584 --> 01:18:45,246
Put it down! Put it down, son.

1050
01:18:45,854 --> 01:18:49,881
-l just wanna go!
-Understandable. Now, put it down.

1051
01:18:50,625 --> 01:18:54,152
-Look, l never meant to hurt anybody!
-Let's keep it that way!

1052
01:18:54,329 --> 01:18:56,229
You surrender, l take you in.

1053
01:18:57,032 --> 01:18:59,728
l know it sounds like a shitty deal,
but you get to live.

1054
01:18:59,935 --> 01:19:03,427
l'll go my way, and you go yours, okay?

1055
01:19:03,605 --> 01:19:08,804
Not gonna happen! You either surrender
or we die where we stand.

1056
01:19:08,977 --> 01:19:11,172
-So, what's it gonna be?
-Sarge!

1057
01:19:24,126 --> 01:19:28,688
l knew if sarge died they'd blame me.
That's why l took Dunbar's dog tags.

1058
01:19:33,235 --> 01:19:35,226
Oh, God! Oh! Oh, God!

1059
01:19:35,403 --> 01:19:39,362
Mueller didn't die after all.
Came after us with a vengeance.

1060
01:19:40,041 --> 01:19:42,339
You know the rest.

1061
01:19:42,978 --> 01:19:46,345
How'd you get Kendall to go along
with switching Dunbar's dog tags?

1062
01:19:46,515 --> 01:19:51,009
l gave him a choice. Either go along
or l drop a dime on his drug scam.

1063
01:19:53,455 --> 01:19:55,446
How about the bodies?

1064
01:19:55,891 --> 01:19:59,258
That hurricane almost lifted
me off the ground.

1065
01:19:59,528 --> 01:20:01,189
But they're out there.

1066
01:20:07,602 --> 01:20:09,866
lt's there, just like you said.

1067
01:20:11,573 --> 01:20:13,507
So you'll testify to all of this?

1068
01:20:14,609 --> 01:20:16,873
l don't think you're gonna get any deals.

1069
01:20:17,412 --> 01:20:19,972
l don't want any deals.

1070
01:20:20,749 --> 01:20:23,377
l'll take him now, if you don't mind.

1071
01:20:31,359 --> 01:20:34,760
We should've died out there
with the others.

1072
01:20:35,463 --> 01:20:37,260
Did you get what you wanted?

1073
01:20:37,465 --> 01:20:39,797
Not even close.

1074
01:20:59,254 --> 01:21:01,882
Just that one thing
that l wanted to ask you about.

1075
01:21:02,057 --> 01:21:04,685
-Say when.
-Yeah, this is Hardy.

1076
01:21:04,860 --> 01:21:06,657
Oh, really?

1077
01:21:07,529 --> 01:21:10,054
Okay. Thank you.

1078
01:21:10,899 --> 01:21:14,733
The kid said that West waited till the
end of the week to tell the colonel.

1079
01:21:14,903 --> 01:21:19,533
Now, why would he wait until
the end of the week to tell you?

1080
01:21:19,708 --> 01:21:23,144
l mean, that doesn't sound
like the West that we knew.

1081
01:21:23,945 --> 01:21:26,311
You think the kid was lying?

1082
01:21:28,083 --> 01:21:31,052
No. l don't.

1083
01:21:32,354 --> 01:21:34,254
-l think you are.
-What?

1084
01:21:34,422 --> 01:21:38,017
l do. l think you're lying. l do.

1085
01:21:38,193 --> 01:21:39,490
l think that....

1086
01:21:39,728 --> 01:21:41,821
-l think that West came to you--
-And?

1087
01:21:42,030 --> 01:21:44,123
And you told Mueller
and Kendall to kill him.

1088
01:21:47,869 --> 01:21:50,133
Then what did l do,
go and poison Kendall?

1089
01:21:50,405 --> 01:21:53,602
-Well, who said he was poisoned?
-What?

1090
01:21:53,808 --> 01:21:57,039
l just found out. The hospital
found out three minutes ago.

1091
01:21:57,212 --> 01:22:01,615
-l was on the phone with the pathologist.
-Golly, Tom, the kid was puking blood...

1092
01:22:01,783 --> 01:22:03,546
...all over the hospital.

1093
01:22:03,718 --> 01:22:06,744
You know, gunshot and childbirth
just didn't seem to fit...

1094
01:22:06,922 --> 01:22:10,619
...so l took a wild-ass fucking guess.

1095
01:22:14,062 --> 01:22:16,929
Was that really the pathologist?

1096
01:22:17,098 --> 01:22:19,293
No, that was my message service.

1097
01:22:19,467 --> 01:22:22,868
Even if it was, does that prove anything?

1098
01:22:23,505 --> 01:22:26,235
You keep forgetting...

1099
01:22:26,408 --> 01:22:27,670
...l don't have to.

1100
01:22:28,843 --> 01:22:32,210
-What?
-l don't have to prove anything...

1101
01:22:32,380 --> 01:22:36,942
-...because it's not my job.
-l mean, golly, Tom....

1102
01:22:37,719 --> 01:22:39,687
l just have to get you
to the real guys.

1103
01:22:42,791 --> 01:22:44,315
One-third.

1104
01:22:51,566 --> 01:22:52,863
Come on, Tom.

1105
01:22:54,102 --> 01:22:56,502
You've never met a bribe you didn't like.

1106
01:22:56,671 --> 01:22:59,834
Oh, l see. l see.

1107
01:23:00,008 --> 01:23:03,637
You called me so in case
l stumbled upon something...

1108
01:23:03,845 --> 01:23:05,244
...you'd just buy me off.

1109
01:23:06,748 --> 01:23:08,739
Crossed my mind.

1110
01:23:10,785 --> 01:23:13,652
Like l said, they were never
gonna make me a general anyway.

1111
01:23:13,822 --> 01:23:15,847
This is about quality of life.

1112
01:23:17,292 --> 01:23:20,728
Tom, you've had a hell of a run of
bad luck. Bounced out of the Army...

1113
01:23:20,895 --> 01:23:24,854
...hanging by a thread at the DEA. You're
gonna wind up a fucking process server.

1114
01:23:25,033 --> 01:23:29,595
lf you lose enough times,
what you are is a loser.

1115
01:23:29,804 --> 01:23:33,001
Why don't you cut yourself a break,
for chrissake? Forty percent.

1116
01:23:33,174 --> 01:23:35,506
Once l'm up and running again.

1117
01:23:35,877 --> 01:23:37,674
Up and running again?

1118
01:23:38,380 --> 01:23:40,780
This is just a hiccup.

1119
01:23:40,949 --> 01:23:44,544
l can get another three, four months
before they close the place down.

1120
01:23:55,764 --> 01:23:57,698
l'll have to think about that.

1121
01:24:16,851 --> 01:24:20,787
And then l saw the gun
and then he drew it...

1122
01:24:20,955 --> 01:24:24,652
...so l had no choice but to fire.

1123
01:24:24,826 --> 01:24:27,590
How many rounds did you fire, captain?

1124
01:24:28,730 --> 01:24:32,063
-Two. Three, maybe.
-Okay.

1125
01:24:32,233 --> 01:24:35,293
All right, ma'am. Thank you.

1126
01:24:46,147 --> 01:24:48,081
Thanks.

1127
01:24:48,516 --> 01:24:50,416
Now what?

1128
01:24:51,186 --> 01:24:56,055
l'm gonna go home and get drunk
and try to forget all of this.

1129
01:24:56,224 --> 01:24:58,419
Well, in that case...

1130
01:24:59,127 --> 01:25:01,186
...there you go.

1131
01:25:03,164 --> 01:25:04,461
Your phone number?

1132
01:25:04,666 --> 01:25:08,067
Yeah, l thought maybe later
l'd slip by and we'd do the old--

1133
01:25:10,538 --> 01:25:14,804
lt's just in case you need me
to testify about the shooting.

1134
01:25:15,310 --> 01:25:18,336
But you don't worry,
they'll clear you on that.

1135
01:25:18,513 --> 01:25:20,640
He was your friend.

1136
01:25:20,815 --> 01:25:22,942
Yeah, but he was
a lot of other things too.

1137
01:25:23,118 --> 01:25:26,110
Besides, my friends don't
betray their country.

1138
01:25:35,263 --> 01:25:37,197
Tuesday?

1139
01:25:38,066 --> 01:25:39,897
Tuesday, pick me up at 7?

1140
01:25:40,702 --> 01:25:44,502
Tuesday at 7. You're one of
the good ones, Osborne.

1141
01:25:44,672 --> 01:25:46,970
l don't want you to worry about
what happened.

1142
01:25:47,142 --> 01:25:50,134
All we gotta do is tell the story right.

1143
01:26:04,826 --> 01:26:07,386
All we gotta do is tell the story right.

1144
01:26:13,334 --> 01:26:18,237
And we can be the men that
took down our sergeant's killers.

1145
01:26:18,406 --> 01:26:21,864
All we gotta do is tell the story....

1146
01:26:22,076 --> 01:26:25,068
-Tell the story right.
-Tell the story right.

1147
01:27:36,484 --> 01:27:38,111
--friends in low places.

1148
01:27:40,355 --> 01:27:42,585
--the murders he's covered up
for his drug dealer?

1149
01:27:44,626 --> 01:27:46,321
--wasn't even his real name.

1150
01:27:47,228 --> 01:27:49,355
Pike wasn't even his real--

1151
01:27:49,564 --> 01:27:52,124
They're dead, right? They're ghosts.

1152
01:27:59,140 --> 01:28:02,109
West trained some of these guys.
And they hated him.

1153
01:28:05,847 --> 01:28:07,610
l wanted him dead--
l wanted him dead--

1154
01:28:09,417 --> 01:28:10,850
l am your objective, right?

1155
01:30:24,118 --> 01:30:25,415
Osborne?

1156
01:30:27,021 --> 01:30:29,251
lf you don't like the music, just say so.

1157
01:30:29,791 --> 01:30:34,922
Don't move. Put your hands
on the table. Now.

1158
01:30:35,296 --> 01:30:36,854
Who are they?

1159
01:30:37,031 --> 01:30:41,695
They are my colleagues. And they're
discussing breakfast recipes.

1160
01:30:42,870 --> 01:30:45,896
-You knew about the coke.
-Yes, l did.

1161
01:30:46,073 --> 01:30:48,132
You knew about Vilmer.

1162
01:30:49,377 --> 01:30:51,607
You knew about Styles.

1163
01:30:52,847 --> 01:30:56,578
ln fact, they work for you,
because you're Section 8.

1164
01:30:56,751 --> 01:31:00,687
You planned all this.
And you killed West.

1165
01:31:01,789 --> 01:31:05,885
Give me one good reason why l should
not fucking blow your head off right now.

1166
01:31:08,362 --> 01:31:10,125
Tom?

1167
01:31:11,132 --> 01:31:14,158
Why did this young woman have
a weapon pointed at your head?

1168
01:31:14,368 --> 01:31:17,826
This is Captain Osborne,
and she has had a long day.

1169
01:31:18,005 --> 01:31:20,633
Oh, l'll bet it was something you said.

1170
01:31:20,842 --> 01:31:23,242
She thinks l killed you.

1171
01:31:24,145 --> 01:31:25,578
He didn't.

1172
01:31:25,780 --> 01:31:27,407
l thought you hated each other.

1173
01:31:27,615 --> 01:31:31,415
l'm not particularly fond of him, and he is
sort of a jerk, but what can you do?

1174
01:31:31,619 --> 01:31:33,951
-Will you cut me some slack?
-Slack?

1175
01:31:34,121 --> 01:31:36,112
Did he say ''slack''?

1176
01:31:36,290 --> 01:31:39,817
Captain. Sit, it's safe.
You wanna talk about slack?

1177
01:31:40,428 --> 01:31:43,625
You take a simple find-out-
who's-working-for-who operation...

1178
01:31:43,798 --> 01:31:47,495
...next thing l know, there's corpses
flopping around like it's raining fish.

1179
01:31:47,702 --> 01:31:49,761
-Yeah, but l rescued your ass.
-Rescued my--?

1180
01:31:49,937 --> 01:31:52,633
-Did my ass need rescuing?
-Don't put me in this.

1181
01:31:52,807 --> 01:31:54,502
You stumble upon a drug operation...

1182
01:31:54,675 --> 01:31:56,768
...in the middle of 10,000
heavily armed men...

1183
01:31:56,944 --> 01:31:58,912
...and you didn't have to be pulled out?

1184
01:31:59,113 --> 01:32:02,571
See now, that's different.
l was going to retire early anyway.

1185
01:32:02,817 --> 01:32:07,015
So you found out about the coke
and you told Styles?

1186
01:32:07,188 --> 01:32:08,553
Yeah, who did nothing.

1187
01:32:08,756 --> 01:32:11,452
Except order Kendall
and Mueller to kill you.

1188
01:32:11,759 --> 01:32:14,489
And you figured that they
were gonna do it in the jungle.

1189
01:32:14,662 --> 01:32:16,960
That's why l called this genius.

1190
01:32:17,164 --> 01:32:21,225
Breakfast is ready! Do you remember
the triplets? Raul's daughters?

1191
01:32:21,402 --> 01:32:24,371
-This is hotter.
-This might eat me!

1192
01:32:25,940 --> 01:32:27,407
Captain.

1193
01:32:27,675 --> 01:32:30,371
Dunbar.
Or is it Pike?

1194
01:32:30,745 --> 01:32:33,305
-Oh, actually it's neither, ma'am.
-Right.

1195
01:32:34,348 --> 01:32:38,717
-So you're not Nunez.
-No, ma'am. l'm afraid l'm not.

1196
01:32:38,886 --> 01:32:43,084
Right. Because none of y'all
exist. You're all dead.

1197
01:32:43,257 --> 01:32:47,785
Well, you could refer to it as
bureaucratic absence of presence.

1198
01:32:47,962 --> 01:32:50,658
l mean, we're here.
But we're not here.

1199
01:32:50,831 --> 01:32:55,291
Now, he would be dead in the ground
if you hadn't saved his ass. l mean dead.

1200
01:32:55,469 --> 01:32:56,936
You are on it today!

1201
01:32:57,138 --> 01:32:58,833
What are you laughing at?

1202
01:32:59,006 --> 01:33:01,497
The idea that you
just transferred into his unit.

1203
01:33:01,676 --> 01:33:04,406
Negative. l just transferred
to Arlington Cemetery.

1204
01:33:04,579 --> 01:33:07,173
You keep talking shit
and you're liable to make roll call.

1205
01:33:08,683 --> 01:33:12,380
-So you're all Section 8?
-l told you she was smart.

1206
01:33:12,553 --> 01:33:15,613
No, you said she was....
What did he say she was?

1207
01:33:15,790 --> 01:33:17,724
-Hot.
-Hot.

1208
01:33:19,660 --> 01:33:21,753
Yes, ma'am. We're officially Section 8.

1209
01:33:22,029 --> 01:33:24,589
And what about the story
about you guys being all...

1210
01:33:24,765 --> 01:33:27,791
-...renegade drug dealers and stuff?
-More like ragamuffins.

1211
01:33:27,969 --> 01:33:30,836
That's been our unit's cover story
since the beginning, ma'am.

1212
01:33:31,005 --> 01:33:34,998
And it's a story that scares
the frijoles out of the Colombians.

1213
01:33:36,911 --> 01:33:40,244
Okay, so now that l know all this,
what happens?

1214
01:33:40,414 --> 01:33:44,544
l get a needle in my arm and wake up
tomorrow morning with no memory?

1215
01:33:44,819 --> 01:33:47,481
lsn't that what you guys do?

1216
01:33:47,722 --> 01:33:51,385
We actually thought you handled
yourself quite well in this situation.

1217
01:33:53,394 --> 01:33:55,919
We were gonna offer you a job.

1218
01:33:57,598 --> 01:34:00,123
Did she tell you the story
about the carnival last night?

1219
01:34:00,334 --> 01:34:02,234
-Oh, don't start.
-Shit.

1220
01:34:02,436 --> 01:34:05,269
-What do you want to know?
-Miss Festival Party Lady.

1221
01:34:05,439 --> 01:34:06,599
What do you wanna know?

1222
01:34:06,774 --> 01:34:09,334
Don't act like you weren't
all over this man.

1223
01:34:09,510 --> 01:34:11,808
Yeah, tell him the truth.

1224
01:34:13,948 --> 01:34:17,577
So, what are you gonna do?

1225
01:34:20,021 --> 01:34:21,716
l think l need a beer.

1226
01:34:23,624 --> 01:34:25,524
Here you go, colonel.

1227
01:34:25,993 --> 01:34:27,324
Colonel?

